to the editor a jan 1 news article reported that american and russian military personnel worked together as the new year approached to monitor the safety of their nuclear missile systems on another page we saw the briefcases with the nuclear codes after they were delivered to russia 's acting president vladimir v putin a man we know little about why not continue the collaboration american experts could accompany the russian briefcases while russians accompanied ours in the event of an accidental alert the russian president would have americans as well as his own staff to consult with in the few minutes that are available to verify an attack with russian early warning systems reportedly in poor shape this might prevent nuclear disaster sayre sheldon arlington mass jan 1 2000

